ata-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cgr1665702879587.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cgr1665702879587.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cgr1665702879587.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cgr1665702879587\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Configuring the COM Connector\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"cgr1665702879587__li_d18017e1_d18018e1_d18019e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To enable COM clients to create instances of Uniface services (call-in), ensure that the exported COM Interface DLL for the service is on the client's workstation.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"cgr1665702879587__li_d18020e1_d18021e1_d18022e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the Uniface COM Configuration utility. Choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">COM Configuration</span> from the Uniface group in the Windows <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Start</span> menu, or run <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucomcfg.exe</span> in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/bin</span> directory of the Uniface installation.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"cgr1665702879587__li_d18023e1_d18024e1_d18025e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">For call-in only, specify options for the COM connector as required, under the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Global Uniface com settings</span>.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgr1665702879587__li_d18026e1_d18027e1_d18028e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Keep COM component in\n\t\t\t memory</span>—keep the COM component in memory when a process repeatedly calls Uniface COM\n\t\t\t objects. This speeds up COM operation and prevents memory leakage, which is particularly useful\n\t\t\t when Uniface services are being called from ASPs. \n\t\t\t <p class=\"p\">The following registry entry is created:</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgr1665702879587__li_d18029e1_d18030e1_d18031e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Debug logging</span>—directs\n\t\t\t the COM connector to generate detailed logging to the Windows debugger channel. The logging is\n\t\t\t output using the Windows API function <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutputDebugString()</code>, so it can be seen while\n\t\t\t running under a debugger such as Visual Studio or Dependency Walker. You can also use DebugView\n\t\t\t from <a class=\"xref\" href=\"http://www.sysinternals.com/\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">www.sysinternals.com</a>. The logging\n\t\t\t can be useful to check the correct working of the other COM options, as well as the general flow of\n\t\t\t COM events. \n\t\t\t <p class=\"p\">The following registry entry is created:</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cgr1665702879587__li_d18032e1_d18033e1_d18034e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Thread\n                        synchronization</span>—causes the COM driver to serialize the\n                     invocation of COM objects, so only one process thread can access a Uniface COM\n                     object at a time. Because Uniface is currently not fully threadsafe, this\n                     option is necessary to make it work in a multi-threaded COM environment without\n                     concurrency problems. <p class=\"p\">The\n                        following registry entry is created:</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"cgr1665702879587__li_d18035e1_d18036e1_d18037e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you selected <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Thread synchronization</span>, edit the assignment file to use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS</span> assignment option:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SETTINGS]\n$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS = 1</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bog1665702719152.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS</a><p>Enable Uniface to handle foreign threads.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526440\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526440\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring the COM Connector Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring the COM Connector The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications. To enable COM clients to create instances of Uniface services (call-in), ensure that the exported COM Interface DLL for the service is on the client's workstation. Run the Uniface COM Configuration utility. Choose COM Configuration from the Uniface group in the Windows Start menu, or run ucomcfg.exe in the /common/bin directory of the Uniface installation. For call-in only, specify options for the COM connector as required, under the Global Uniface com settings . Keep COM component in memory —keep the COM component in memory when a process repeatedly calls Uniface COM objects. This speeds up COM operation and prevents memory leakage, which is particularly useful when Uniface services are being called from ASPs. The following registry entry is created: Debug logging —directs the COM connector to generate detailed logging to the Windows debugger channel. The logging is output using the Windows API function OutputDebugString() , so it can be seen while running under a debugger such as Visual Studio or Dependency Walker. You can also use DebugView from www.sysinternals.com . The logging can be useful to check the correct working of the other COM options, as well as the general flow of COM events. The following registry entry is created: Thread synchronization —causes the COM driver to serialize the invocation of COM objects, so only one process thread can access a Uniface COM object at a time. Because Uniface is currently not fully threadsafe, this option is necessary to make it work in a multi-threaded COM environment without concurrency problems. The following registry entry is created: If you selected Thread synchronization , edit the assignment file to use the $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS assignment option: [SETTINGS] $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS = 1 Copy Related Links $ALLOW_FOREIGN_THREADS Enable Uniface to handle foreign threads. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}